      • ensureCapacity

        private void ensureCapacity​(int minCapacity)
        Ensures that the internal array has enough capacity to accommodate at least a specified minimum of elements which is the parameter. if the old capacity is less than the minimum, then it doubles the old capacity. Then creates a new array of type `Object` with the new capacity as the size, and copies the current element in the array into the new one.
        Parameters:
        minCapacity - the minimum capacity that the array is supposed to hold.
